On Thu, Nov 9, 2017 at 6:18 PM, abaviska ***@***.***> wrote:
 Hi, I am trying to setup tensorflow with Python 3.6 using this wheel on
 windows CPU version. tensorflow-1.4.0-cp36-cp36m-win_amd64.whl. But, It
 is giving an error like Could not find a version that satisfies the
 requirement wheel>=0.26 (from tensorflow==0.12.0) (from versions: )
 o matching distribution found for wheel>=0.26 (from tensorflow==0.12.0).

 I can install on Mac but failing on windows. Can anyone help.?
